# UI/UX — Nielsen heuristics

Every UI/UX change MUST be reviewed against Nielsen's 10 usability heuristics before merge.

## UI Elements Gallery (mandatory)

**Before creating or changing any UI element**, read [docs/ui-elements-gallery.md](../../docs/ui-elements-gallery.md):

1. Find an existing element to reuse (class, Material component, behavior).
2. Match documented **properties**, **style** (tokens/classes), and **behavior**.
3. If no element fits, add the new element to the gallery in the same PR.
4. Do not introduce ad-hoc buttons, colors, or form patterns outside the gallery.

## Checklist (per screen or flow)

| # | Heuristic | Issues application |
|---|-----------|-------------------|
| 1 | **Visibility of system status** | Loading/disabled during submit; notification badge; kanban drop feedback; toasts |
| 2 | **Match system / real world** | Domain terms from [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md); PT-BR labels; familiar tracker patterns (Kanban, ticket ID) |
| 3 | **User control & freedom** | Cancel/close on dialogs; back navigation; logout; avoid `disableClose` unless required |
| 4 | **Consistency & standards** | Gallery elements + `styles.scss`; same button hierarchy; no one-off hex colours |
| 5 | **Error prevention** | `mat-form-field` validation; confirm destructive actions |
| 6 | **Recognition over recall** | Visible nav, status filter, project cards — minimise memory load |
| 7 | **Flexibility & efficiency** | Header search; Enter on search; role-based menu shortcuts |
| 8 | **Aesthetic & minimalist** | Corporate palette in `colors.scss`; content over decoration; clear hierarchy |
| 9 | **Error recovery** | `.error` messages; toasts; empty states with next-step guidance |
| 10 | **Help & documentation** | Footer OpenAPI link; empty states; tooltips where labels are ambiguous |

## Corporate visual language

Tokens: `src/main/webui/src/colors.scss` and `src/main/webui/src/styles.scss`. Full element mapping: [ui-elements-gallery.md](../../docs/ui-elements-gallery.md).

| Role | Token / pattern |
|------|-----------------|
| Chrome (header, footer) | `$base-background-color` |
| Primary action | `$base-active-color` + `.btn` |
| Secondary action | `.btn-secondary` |
| Destructive | `.btn-cancel` / `$base-error-color` |
| Page background | `$surface-page` |
| Cards / panels | `$surface-card` + `$shadow-card` |

**Do:** restrained neutrals, 4px radius, Roboto, muted table zebra, accessible focus rings.  
**Don't:** ad-hoc Bootstrap blues, pink/red row alternation, coral focus rings, playful card lift, personal branding in prod chrome.

## Before finishing a UI change

1. Confirm gallery compliance (reuse or extend [ui-elements-gallery.md](../../docs/ui-elements-gallery.md)).
2. Walk the Nielsen checklist for the affected flow.
3. Extend `colors.scss` / `styles.scss` — avoid scattered hex in component SCSS.
4. Verify mobile (`@media max-width: 750px` in `styles.scss`).
5. Run affected `*.spec.ts` when behaviour changes.
6. Update [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) when routes or labels change.

